  83:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****           and the Callback ID.
  84:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****           This function allows to reset following callbacks:
  85:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) TxCpltCallback        : SPI Tx Completed callback
  86:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) RxCpltCallback        : SPI Rx Completed callback
  87:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) TxRxCpltCallback      : SPI TxRx Completed callback
  88:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) TxHalfCpltCallback    : SPI Tx Half Completed callback
  89:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) RxHalfCpltCallback    : SPI Rx Half Completed callback
  90:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) TxRxHalfCpltCallback  : SPI TxRx Half Completed callback
  91:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) ErrorCallback         : SPI Error callback
  92:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) AbortCpltCallback     : SPI Abort callback
  93:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) SuspendCallback       : SPI Suspend callback
  94:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) MspInitCallback       : SPI Msp Init callback
  95:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****             (++) MspDeInitCallback     : SPI Msp DeInit callback
  96:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c **** 
  97:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        By default, after the HAL_SPI_Init() and when the state is HAL_SPI_STATE_RESET
  98:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
  99:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        examples HAL_SPI_MasterTxCpltCallback(), HAL_SPI_MasterRxCpltCallback().
 100:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 101:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_SPI_Init()/ HAL_SPI_DeInit() only when
 102:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 103:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        If MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_SPI_Init()/ HAL_SPI_DeInit()
 104:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state
 105:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 106:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_SPI_STATE_READY state only.
 107:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 108:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        in HAL_SPI_STATE_READY or HAL_SPI_STATE_RESET state,
 109:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 110:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 111:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        using HAL_SPI_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_SPI_DeInit()
 112:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        or HAL_SPI_Init() function.
 113:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 114:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        When The compilation define USE_HAL_PPP_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or not defined,
 115:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        the callback registering feature is not available and weak callbacks are used.
 116:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 117:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        SuspendCallback restriction:
 118:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****            SuspendCallback is called only when MasterReceiverAutoSusp is enabled and
 119:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        EOT interrupt is activated. SuspendCallback is used in relation with functions
 120:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****        HAL_SPI_Transmit_IT, HAL_SPI_Receive_IT and HAL_SPI_TransmitReceive_IT.
 121:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 122:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****     [..]
 123:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****       Circular mode restriction:
 124:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****       (+) The DMA circular mode cannot be used when the SPI is configured in these modes:
 125:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****           (++) Master 2Lines RxOnly
 126:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****           (++) Master 1Line Rx
 127:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****       (+) The CRC feature is not managed when the DMA circular mode is enabled
 128:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****       (+) The functions HAL_SPI_DMAPause()/ HAL_SPI_DMAResume() are not supported. Return always
 129:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****           HAL_ERROR with ErrorCode set to HAL_SPI_ERROR_NOT_SUPPORTED.
 130:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c ****           Those functions are maintained for backward compatibility reasons.
 131:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_spi.c **** 
